At this point, this information would be synced back to the UI via the &quot;main game loop&quot;, but in your case that would probably just mean taking the latest response and updating the &quot;remote player&quot; information on the `Display`.

Realistically, you should have a `Player` class, you&#39;d then pass two instances to `Display`, one representing the local player and one representing the remote player.

